Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 27a, 28. Name Archokrates. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0099.01 and British Museum 2011,5003.69.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0704)
